Horizon Global Corporation Key Developments

Horizon Global Corporation Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended March 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Second Quarter, First Half and Year Ending December 31, 2017
May 3 17
Horizon Global Corporation reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company reported net sales of $203,280,000 compared to $146,110,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $660,000 compared to operating profit of $7,810,000 a year ago. Loss before income tax was $11,740,000 compared to income before income tax of $2,930,000 a year ago. Net loss attributable to the company was $9,860,000 or $0.41 per basic and diluted share compared to net income attributable to the company of 2,190,000 or $0.12 per basic and diluted share a year ago. Net cash used for operating activities was $40,120,000 compared to $23,580,000 a year ago. Capital expenditures were $7,510,000 compared to $3,420,000 a year ago. Adjusted net loss was $4,060,000 or $0.17 per share compared to adjusted net income of $2,780,000 or $0.15 per share a year ago.

For the year ending December 31, 2017, the company expects revenue of $844,000 to $876,400, operating profit of $40,000 to $46,000, adjusted operating profit of $53,000 to 59,000, operating cash between $40.0 million and $50.0 million, diluted EPS of $0.50 to $0.60, and adjusted diluted EPS of $0.94 to $1.04. Adjusted effective tax expected between 0% and 5% for the year on a full year basis.

For the second quarter of 2017, the company expects revenues between $235 million to $245 million, diluted EPS of $0.61 to $0.66, and adjusted diluted EPS of $0.67 to $0.72.

For the first half of 2017, the company expects diluted EPS of $0.23 to $0.28, adjusted diluted EPS of $0.52 to $0.57.


